events.33: Origins of the Coptic Orthodox Church.
events.642: Mosque of Amr ibn al-As built.
events.970: Misr al-Qahira settlement founded by Fatimid Al-Mu'izz li-Din Allah.
events.1168: Egypt's capital moved from Fustat to Cairo.
events.1176: Cairo was unsuccessfully attacked in the Crusades.
events.1250: City becomes capital of Mamluk Sultanate.
events.1517: Capture of Cairo by Ottoman forces. City becomes provincial capital during Selim I's rule of Ottoman Empire.
events.1801: June: Siege of Cairo – French surrender to British and Ottoman forces.
events.1863: Museum of Egyptian antiquities founded at Bulak.
events.1919: Uprising against British occupation. American University in Cairo established.
